race.description: In Loving Memory Of Barbara Runciman F&M Mdn Plate
race.comment: HERMIONE PRANCER (4) third-up for this and comes back a level after failing to close off in town. Stalked the speed from the right draw when a battling seventh over 1400m at Warwick Farm in a Super Maiden. Will relish Grima's claim and can finish over the top of these. MARK OF GLORY (6) returned from a let-up at her second race start when raced on the speed before fading in the straight to finish seventh over 1350m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Suited back to this trip from the good gate. Will find this easier. PAZYRYK (9) resumed from a lengthy break with an eye catching fourth over 1100m at Gosford. Will have little trouble running the trip and can overcome the sticky gate. IN LIMBO (5) covered plenty of ground on resumption when a tiring eighth over 1200m at Canterbury. Gets a better set up for this and sure to be thereabouts. MEDITERRA (7) Snitzel filly who comes here with a distinct fitness edge over the bulk of these fourth-up. Will run the trip from the low gate.
